# Project Memory — InstaGold (Gold)

## App Identity
- App name: **InstaGold** (package: com.ibrahym.goldfamily)
- Platform: **Android only** — ignore iOS for UI, testing, screenshots
- APK outputs at repo root: **`InstaGold-dev.apk`** (dev flavor, test ads, label "InstaGold Dev") via `./scripts/build-dev-apk.sh`; **`InstaGold.apk`** (prod) via `./scripts/build-and-upload.sh` or `flutter build apk --flavor prod`
- Play Store bundle: `./scripts/build-play-aab.sh` → `app-prod-release.aab`
- Play prep: `PLAY_STORE_PREP.md`; owner checklist `YOUR_ACTIONS_BEFORE_PLAY.md`; privacy draft `docs/PRIVACY_POLICY_TEMPLATE.md`; `scripts/print-release-signing-fingerprints.sh` for Firebase SHA
- Firebase project: goldcalculate
- **Build commands ALWAYS require `--flavor dev|prod`** — never build without flavor

## Architecture
- Monorepo: `scraper-service/` (price scraping), `main-backend/` (API), `flutter-app/` (mobile UI)
- Mobile mode: local SQLite + direct scraping — no backend servers needed on device
- Web mode: talks to main-backend HTTP APIs
- No CI/CD pipelines

## STRICT Design Rules (MANDATORY — never skip)

### Logo
- Use ONLY the provided IG monogram image (`assets/icons/ig_logo.png`) — NEVER use Material icons as brand placeholder
- Logo MUST appear in:
  - App header (top-left, size 36+)
  - Login screen (centered, 100x100, gold glow shadow)
  - Splash screen (Android native mipmap `launch_image`)
  - Empty states (subtle, low opacity ~0.35)
  - Android launcher icon (all densities via `flutter_launcher_icons`)

### Dark Mode (CRITICAL — must NOT be flat)
- Base: `#0B0B0D` with layered gradients using deep gold/brown tones (`#12100C`, `#14110D`)
- Vertical warm gradient overlay with gold-tinted bands
- **Visible flowing wave patterns** — gold/dark-gold tones, multiple flowing curves, `CustomPaint` in `PremiumBackground` widget
- Radial gold glow highlights behind key areas (headers, cards)
- Section cards use gradient dark background (`#1C1916` → `#181614`), gold border `0.10` alpha
- **FAIL condition: flat black background = WRONG**

### Gold Styling
- Primary accent: `#D4AF37`, deep `#C9A227`, light `#E8CD5A`, muted `#B8962E`
- Always use **gradient gold** — never flat gold
- Price cards: 3-4 stop gold gradient, soft glow `boxShadow`, rounded corners 20px
- Buttons: gold gradient (`#E8CD5A → #D4AF37 → #C9A227`), glow shadow, dark text on button
- `FilledButton` and `ElevatedButton` theme: gold background with dark foreground

### Cards & UI
- Cards: gradient gold for price cards, gradient dark for section cards
- Soft glow or elevation (gold-tinted shadow in dark mode)
- Rounded corners (20-22px)
- Gold accent gradient bar on section headers

### Navigation
- Floating glassmorphism pill-shaped bottom nav
- Dark glass surface in dark mode (`kDarkCard` at 0.85 alpha)
- Gold border (0.08 alpha) in dark mode
- `BackdropFilter` blur (sigmaX/Y: 20)
- Gold active indicator and label

### Background Widget
- `PremiumBackground` wraps both `DashboardScreen` and `LoginScreen`
- Only active in dark mode; light mode passes child through
- Located at `lib/widgets/premium_background.dart`

## UI Design Decisions
- Price cards: gold gradient rounded rectangles, drag-and-drop reorderable
- Home layout: 21K full-width hero → 24K full-width hero → 14K+18K row → Pound+Ounce row
- Gap card: full-width tinted box (green/red), EGP gap value large and centred, tappable for explanation popup
- Ounce card: shiny gold gradient
- Asset cards: icon in gold circle (ClipOval for PNGs), title, karat/weight/date subtitle, Purchase/Current/Profit rows with %
- Empty states: IG logo at low opacity + gold gradient "Add" button
- No custom ClipPath shapes — standard rounded containers only

## Code Patterns
- Dialog builders: always use builder context (`ctx`) for AppStrings, Theme, Navigator — never State's `context`
- Member: name field only, no relation field. API `addMember`/`updateMember` have optional relation param
- Localization: `AppStrings.t(context, 'key')` — Arabic and English
- Colors: `withValues(alpha: ...)` not deprecated `withOpacity`
- Theme variant: `kUiDesignVariant` in `ui_design_variant.dart` — set to `classic` to rollback

